name: SPECIAL LIVERY? WestJet "Think Green Fly Clean" 737-700 Landing at Calgary Airport
description:
Thank you to RadarBox for supporting this plane spotting video! Find out more about them at https://www.radarbox.com/?referrer=AlexAviation

Back in November, this WestJet 737-700 mysteriously relocated to Chicago-Rockford Airport for several months, undergoing a couple test flights there.

It flew back to Canada earlier this week, with some structural modifications made to the rear wing root and the flap track fairings, along with some titles - "Think Green Fly Clean", and "Aero Design Labs".

What's odd is that there's been pretty much no public information on this project. However, Aero Design Labs is a company that's "focused on drag reduction" (https://www.jsfirm.com/Aero+Design+Labs/19557/companyprofile) so presumably this 737 has been acting as a test bed of sorts.

Either way, kind of an interesting catch, and (sort of) a new special livery for Canadian spotters to keep an eye on!
